{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":3,"markdown":"Nationally, ANC1 vs. ANC4 consistency is very high (97%), but delivery vs. BCG (81%) and Penta1 vs. Penta3 (81%) show weaker alignment.

Across districts, consistency varies widely, with several districts falling below 80% for delivery vs. BCG and Penta1 vs. Penta3 consistency.

The most inconsistent results are in Western Area Urban, Western Area Rural, and Bonthe districts, underscoring where data plausibility checks are most critical."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"82dd639f-c137-43aa-87a5-53c455989ee3","moduleId":"m001","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Internal consistency"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"BCG doses rose steadily from ~23,000 in mid-2023 to ~26,000 by September 2025, showing a smoother and more gradual rise compared to the pentavalent series.

Penta1 and Penta3 followed very similar patterns over time, with parallel rises and dips. By September 2025, Penta1 reached ~29,500, while Penta3 was ~30,200 — maintaining a modest 8–10% dropout between first and third doses.

Overall, immunization shows a clear upward trajectory. Addressing the modest gap between Penta1 and Penta3 remains important to ensure full protection.","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false},{"type":"figure","presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"2e8e89f6-e7cd-4eb0-924f-268146132ae8","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""},"stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Trends in child immunization","useFooter":false,"footerText":""}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"Postpartum acceptors decreased steadily from around 10,000 in early 2023 to about 7,000 by 2025, showing a consistent downward trend.

Postpartum family planning counselling remained higher throughout the period and increased gradually, rising from roughly 17,000–19,000 in 2023 to over 22,000–24,000 by 2025.

